06/02/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Border police arrested Serbian war crimes suspect Mile Letica on Tuesday (February 5th) as he tried to enter Croatia at the Ilok Mile border checkpoint. His arrest was based on an international warrant issued by the Sisak County Court. The former Yugoslav National Army captain is suspected of crimes against civilians in 1991, at the beginning of the war in Croatia. (HINA, Javno.com, Beta, B92 - 05/02/08)
